                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/22568",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=peptolab",
                        "name": "peptolab",
                        "displayName": "Simon Mundy",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Julian\n\nI'm looking into this for the 1.6 release if it's able to be resolved. Can I clarify - what is the reason for explicitly casting as a string by default? The only concern I have defaulting to a string type is that it will break an existing expected behaviour. Or is SQLite expecting a string and this behaviour has always been incorrect.\n\nThe patch itself is straight-forward, as are the tests, but I want to be sure this is absolutely required before committing.\n",
